<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic"><gloss type="from">Prime Minister
                                        Churchill</gloss> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quebec</hi></placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-16">September 16, 1944</date>.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. President</hi>. I return the Memorandum you
                                gave me about Italian Colonies.<note n="1" xml:id="d243fn1">The
                                    paper attached to this communication is the ribbon copy of
                                    Hull’s memorandum to Roosevelt of September 11, 1944, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_408">p.
                                    408</ref>.</note></p>
                            <p>The Foreign Office would like to treat this as an official
                                communication if you would allow us to keep a copy of it.<note n="2" xml:id="d243fn2">Attnched to this memorandum in the Roosevelt
                                    Papers is the following handwritten note: “The President told
                                    the <gloss target="#t_PM1">P. M.</gloss> OK to keep copies of
                                    attached &amp; he also said he wanted an answer from the British
                                    on it. D[<hi rend="smallcaps">orothy</hi>] J B[<hi rend="smallcaps">rady</hi>].”</note></p>
                            <p>It seems that the usual broad and substantial measure of agreement
                                exists between us, but we should like to look into the details more
                                closely.</p>
                            <closer><signed>W[<hi rend="smallcaps">inston</hi>] S C[<hi rend="smallcaps">hurchill</hi>]</signed><lb/>16.9.44.</closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>